# cPanel Preferences

## Change cPanel User Password

- Log on to cPanel
- Under Preference click on Change Password

```diagram

```

- Fillup the password change form and click on Change your password now!.
- Also tick option Allow MySQL password change

```diagram

```

You can also watch Video Tutorial from cPanel related to password reset.

## Change Language of cPanel Interface

- Log on to cPanel
- Click on Change Language under Preference 

```diagram

```

- Select the language from the Drop down list and then click Change

```diagram

```


## cPanel Video Tutorials

The section includes video tutorials on the cPanel options which is provided by cPanel. Follow the steps to watch video tutorials

- Login to cPanel of your account
- Under Preferences click on Video Tutorials

```diagram

```

- A new page will open with video tutorial. These tutorials allow you to easily learn as you can rewind, pause, and fast forward through any of the videos.

```diagram

```

## Change Style of cPanel Interface

- Login to cPanel of your account
- Under Preferences click on Change Style.

```diagram

```

- Select your style from the list and click Switch button
This feature allows the overall look and feel of cPanel to be altered to fit your personal style. Several pre-installed styles are available to choose from

```diagram

```
